cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR. 

The paper deals with the physical layer abstraction model for 5G New Radio (NR) and its integration into an open-source ns-3 based NR system-level simulator. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 

- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the simulation of 5G networks and their performance. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) as it considers the signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) mapping and SINR-block error rate (BLER) lookup tables for various NR configurations. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it presents a system-level simulator for 5G NR networks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) as it deals with the modulation and coding schemes used in 5G NR networks. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it may involve the hardware architecture of 5G NR networks.
